The '''Tennessee Cave Salamander''' ('''''Gyrinophilus palleucus''''') is a species of [[salamander]] in the [[Plethodontidae]] family.
It is [[Endemism|endemic]] to the [[United States]].
[[Category:Fauna of the United States]]
Its natural [[habitat]]s are inland [[karst]]s and [[cave]]s.
It is threatened by [[habitat loss]].
